So the AuthCommand is a really complex model, that is binding a ton of stuff. The withSecurity thing makes sure they have permission to update the password for that object. But because grails databinding is so powerful, it could in theory have updated a bunch of stuff in that model that they have no right to be updating. And because those objects are now in the session, when the transaction ends, those rogue updates would be updated too.

What I want to be able to do is just say to hibernate, ok I only want to save changes to the m.personalC.self object. Anything else in the session, ignore.

Is there any way to do that?

